nd Google Play Partner Center.Roles & Privileges: Admins are granted permissions to "transfer licenses" and "manage volume purchases" within their assigned silos, ensuring they cannot interfere with other admins' catalogs.Metadata and Bulk Upload ProtocolsFor a catalog of 100+ titles per admin, the "ONIX 3.0" standard is the required communication protocol. Metadata must be "structured meticulously" to ensure discoverability across the supply chain.Metadata Field2026 Optimization Strategy Title/SubtitleShift from keywords to "Conversational Queries" (GEO-optimized).Series DataEssential for linking the 108 books; must follow Author/Series/Volume hierarchy.KeywordsMust include "AI Narrated" and specific persona-targeted jargon (e.g., "first reps").BISAC CodesDeep categorization into micro-niches (e.g., BUS071000 for M&A).DescriptionMust begin with the mandatory "Digital Voice" disclaimer for Apple.Admins utilize "ONIXEDIT for Windows" or "ONIXEDIT Cloud" to maintain metadata compliance. This software allows for the "Automated management of cover images" and "Integrated ONIX validation," ensuring that the 2,160 titles meet the major world standards for bibliographic data without manual XML coding.Financial Management: Royalty Automation and OptimizationThe ultimate goal of the 20-admin deployment is the creation of a "Digital Asset" that earns monthly royalties without ongoing client management. In 2026, managing royalties for 2,160 titles across multiple platforms is a significant logistical challenge, necessitating the use of "Royalty Tracker" software.The Findaway Voices MultiplierFindaway Voices (now integrated with Spotify) serves as the primary distribution hub for the wide catalog. They pay authors 80% of the revenue received from retailers.Sale TypeExpected Author Share (80% of Net) A-la-Carte Retail40% - 50% of List PriceSubscription (Pool)30% - 40% of List PriceLibrary License30% - 50% of List PriceSpotify (Direct)50% - 60% of Net SalesBy distributing "wide,"