in v4 are we addressing good: [When it comes to **self-help audiobooks**, *who the author appears to be* matters a **lot** \'97 because readers and listeners don\'92t just want ideas and advice, they want to *trust* the person delivering them. That trust influences whether they *believe the content*, *feel connected*, and *recommend it to others*. ([The Self-Publishing Advice Center][1])\
