Continue using author metadata for story writing (specific_struggles, location, background).\
Optionally frame some stories as \'93from the author\'92s perspective\'94 or \'93author\'92s experience\'94 in the narration so the guide feels like a real person with experience, not just a generic narrator.\
D. Transparency\
Add an optional, configurable line (e.g. in A0 or in app metadata): e.g. \'93This work was created with AI assistance and curated for your benefit,\'94 or similar, so we\'92re \'93thoughtful about AI transparency\'94 without undermining trust.\
E. Author-consistent voice across the book\
In V4 (and any manifest 
\f8 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  assembly path), consider: (1) passing author_id (and maybe author tones/domains) into section/story selection or framing, and (2) ensuring intro + body + conclusion feel like one person\'92s tone and values, not just \'93persona + topic.\'94\
