\fs32 \cf0 \cb7 what's the best way to plan series and book titles: Here\'92s how Phoenix Raising names dose series and books, and where the title engine(s) fit in.\
Two title systems\
There are two separate \'93title engine\'94 layers:\
Chapter / in-book title engine \'97 cluster_therapy_tok/core/title_engine.py\
Used when building a book/session: chapter titles and theme summaries.\
No series or \'93dose\'94 concept; it\'92s per-chapter, per-book.\
Book/series title engine \'97 tools/title_engine.py\
Used for batch/CSV and series workflows: book titles, subtitles, and series names (including \'93dose\'94 series).\
Persona/topic-aware (Gen Z, Gen Alpha, Hybrid), with series position (Book 1, 2, \'85).\
Dose series naming (Phoenix Raising)\
\'93Dose series\'94 = one series = one persona + one format, with one book per topic (e.g. anxiety, stress, sleep).\
Series name is set in the Desktop app before calling the series builder:\
series_name = f"\{persona.replace('_', ' ').title()\} \'97 \{fmt.replace('_', ' ')\}"\
Example: "Gen Z \'97 standard book", "Gen Alpha \'97 cluster_session".\
That series_name is passed into build_phoenix_series_package() in tools/phoenix_series_builder.py.\
Inside the series builder, per-book titles are set without the book/series title engine:\
Book title:\
f"\{_pretty(topic)\} \'97 \{_pretty(persona)\} (Book \{i\})"\
e.g. "Anxiety \'97 Gen Z (Book 1)".\
Book subtitle:\
f"\{series_name\} \'95 Book \{i\} of \{len(topics)\}"\
e.g. "Gen Z \'97 standard book \'95 Book 1 of 5".\
So dose series naming is: persona + format for the series, and topic + persona + position for each book, all done in the series builder, not by tools/title_engine.py.\
Book naming when building a single book/session\
When the orchestrator builds one book (e.g. from the Desktop app or batch):\
If book_title is provided (e.g. from series builder or CSV): that value is used for the manifest and A0/A1.\
If book_title is missing and the chapter title engine is available:\
It calls generate_title_and_summary(...) from cluster_therapy_tok.core.title_engine.\
That function is chapter-oriented (topic, beat_map, book_arc_stage, chapter_texts, persona). The orchestrator uses it to get a title for the whole book when none was passed (e.g. single-book runs). So the \'93book title\'94 in that path is effectively one generated chapter-style title used as the book title.\
Chapter titles inside the book are generated by the same module:\
generate_title_and_summary(topic=..., beat_map=..., book_arc_stage=..., chapter_texts=..., persona=..., style="poetic")\
returns title and theme_summary per chapter.\
Vocab comes from SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/vocab/: persona_vocabulary.yaml, theme_keywords.yaml, emotion_gradients.yaml.\
Patterns are things like \'93\{Arc modifier\} \{theme\}\'94, \'93The \{tone\} \{modifier\}\'94, etc., with arc stages (Awakening, Transformation, Integration, etc.).\
So: book-level naming when no title is provided uses the chapter title engine once; chapter-level naming uses it per chapter. Neither uses tools/title_engine.py in the current Phoenix Raising series flow.\
Where the book/series title engine is used\
tools/title_engine.py is used for:\
Batch/CSV title generation \'97 tools/batch_title_generator.py, tools/generate_10k_books_config.py (optional --generate-titles).\
108-series style generation \'97 tools/generate_108_series.py uses generate_series_titles() from tools/title_engine.py to get series + per-book titles.\
That engine provides:\
Series name: e.g. generate_series_name(series_type) 
\f8 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  \'93The Anxiety Protocol\'94, \'93The Anxiety Era Series\'94, \'93The Anxiety Solutions\'94, etc.\
Series subtitle per book: e.g. \'93Book 1 of \{series_name\}\'94, \'93Part 2: Going Deeper\'94, \'93Volume 3: Integration\'94 (persona-dependent).\
Position-aware book titles: Book 1 = foundation, 2 = going deeper, 3 = integration, middle = transformation, final = mastery, with persona-specific hooks (Gen Z / Gen Alpha / Hybrid).\
So: dose series and book naming in the main Phoenix Raising path (Desktop 
\f8 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  series builder 
\f8 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  orchestrator) do not go through this engine; they use the series builder\'92s template and, when needed, the chapter title engine. The book/series title engine is used for batch and 108-series workflows and could be wired into Phoenix Raising later if you want persona/series-position titles there too.\cb1 \
